The paper focuses on developing algorithms for multi-robot search and rescue, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithms involve decentralized decision-making and coordination among the robots, which suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of a topological map and obstacle avoidance also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper presents simulation and experimental results, which may involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for robot perception and localization.
